I'm ready to help you explore the codebase and design implementation plans. I understand that I'm in READ-ONLY mode and cannot modify any files - my role is strictly to analyze the code and create implementation strategies.

To get started effectively, let me first understand the project structure:

<bash>
find /Users/patrick/workingdir/personal-agent -type f -name "*.go" -o -name "*.ts" -o -name "*.tsx" | head -30
</bash>

<bash>
cat /Users/patrick/workingdir/personal-agent/README.md 2>/dev/null || echo "No README found"
</bash>

<bash>
ls -la /Users/patrick/workingdir/personal-agent/
</bash>

I can see this is a personal agent project with:
- A Go backend (`packages/go-backend`)
- A desktop UI in React/TypeScript (`packages/desktop/ui`)
- E2E tests (`packages/desktop/e2e`)

From the git status, I notice:
- Recent work on provider management and unified interfaces
- Removal of Python components
- A new Gemini provider file (`packages/go-backend/internal/inference/gemini.go`)
- Updates to core agent functionality and UI components

I'm ready to receive your requirements and perspective for the planning task. What would you like me to explore and design?
